<div id="c10">
<p>I agree that some of the recent literature ostensibly about skepticism might be at least part of what you&#8217;re looking for. They might include more examples of bad thinking than good, but not exclusively. In addition to Shermer&#8217;s Why People Believe Weird Things, I recommend Carl Sagan&#8217;s last two books, The Demon-Haunted World and Billions and Billions.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://collopy.net/">Peter Collopy</a>
 on December 16, 2006 <a href="thinkbetter#c10" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
